Here are JSON examples for all operations related to Employee-Project Mapping, including saving data, assigning projects to employees, and assigning employees to projects.


---

1️⃣ Save a New Employee

API Endpoint: POST /employees

JSON Input:

{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "address": {
        "city": "New York",
        "state": "NY",
        "pinCode": 10001
    },
    "skills": ["Java", "Spring Boot"],
    "employmentHistories": [
        {
            "companyName": "Tech Corp",
            "experience": 3,
            "jobTitle": "Software Engineer"
        },
        {
            "companyName": "Innovate Ltd",
            "experience": 2,
            "jobTitle": "Backend Developer"
        }
    ]
}


---

2️⃣ Save a New Project

API Endpoint: POST /projects

JSON Input:

{
    "projectName": "AI Development"
}


---

3️⃣ Assign Projects to an Employee

API Endpoint: PUT /employees/{id}/assign-projects
(Replace {id} with an actual Employee ID)

JSON Input:

[1, 2, 3]  // Assign projects with IDs 1, 2, and 3 to the employee


---

4️⃣ Assign Employees to a Project

API Endpoint: PUT /projects/{id}/assign-employees
(Replace {id} with an actual Project ID)

JSON Input:

[4, 5, 6]  // Assign employees with IDs 4, 5, and 6 to the project


---

5️⃣ Retrieve an Employee with Projects

API Endpoint: GET /employees/{id}
(Replace {id} with an actual Employee ID)

Example Response:

{
    "id": 1,
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "address": {
        "city": "New York",
        "state": "NY",
        "pinCode": 10001
    },
    "skills": ["Java", "Spring Boot"],
    "employmentHistories": [
        {
            "companyName": "Tech Corp",
            "experience": 3,
            "jobTitle": "Software Engineer"
        }
    ],
    "projects": [
        {
            "id": 1,
            "projectName": "AI Development"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "projectName": "Cloud Migration"
        }
    ]
}


---

6️⃣ Retrieve a Project with Employees

API Endpoint: GET /projects/{id}
(Replace {id} with an actual Project ID)

Example Response:

{
    "id": 1,
    "projectName": "AI Development",
    "employees": [
        {
            "id": 4,
            "name": "Alice Smith"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "name": "Bob Johnson"
        }
    ]
}


---

Final Steps

1. First, save an employee and a project using POST requests.


2. Then, assign projects to employees using PUT /employees/{id}/assign-projects.


3. Or assign employees to projects using PUT /projects/{id}/assign-employees.


4. Retrieve employee and project details using GET requests.



This structure allows full control over employee-project assignments. Let me know if you need any modifications!

